Setup instructions:

1. Get a fresh build of Eclipse Indigo for Java
2. Install M2Eclipse
3. Install Scala-IDE for 2.8
4. Edit the pom.xml here to make sense for you.
5. File > Import > Existing Maven Project > this folder
6. Restart Eclipse

Thanks to:
- http://whileonefork.blogspot.com/2011/06/beginning-scala-building-project-with.html
- http://www.valleyprogramming.com/blog/2011/scala-maven-eclipse-scalatest-colorado